OL,4,Care 'a betrayal', victim says
OL,6,FVictims of the infected blood scandal
OL,7,Fsay they are frustrated that the
OL,8,Fgovernment has still not paid them the
OL,9,Fcompensation that they were promised.
OL,11,FJoan Edgington from Watchet is one of
OL,12,Fthe 30,000 people in the UK who were
OL,13,Fgiven treatments infected with HIV and
OL,14,Fhepatitis C during the 1970s and 80s.
OL,16,FSome 3,000 people died as a result and
OL,17,Fsurvivors are living with lifelong
OL,18,Fhealth implications.
OL,20,FJoan underwent surgery in 1991 and
OL,21,Freceived a blood transfusion.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/9
