OL,3,CDelays to infected blood compensation
OL,4,Care 'a betrayal', victim says
OL,6,FThe long-awaited report last year
OL,7,Foutlined how 30,000 people in the UK
OL,8,Fcontracted HIV, hepatitis C and other
OL,9,Fdiseases through contaminated blood
OL,10,Fproducts between the 1970s and early
OL,11,F1990s.
OL,13,FThe report's author, Sir Brian
OL,14,FLangstaff found "systemic, collective
OL,15,Fand individual failures" by government
OL,16,Fdepartments and various parts of the
OL,17,FNHS led to a "calamity" that has so
OL,18,Ffar claimed more than 3,000 lives and
OL,19,F"destroyed friendships, families (and)
OL,20,Ffinances".
